e-to-sigkill-on-shutdown\" rel=\"nofollow\" title=\"Frequent escalate to SIGKILL on shutdown\" class=\"ap-connect-link\"><s>#441</s></a>).</p>\n<p>In testing while preparing <a href=\"#!/osrf/gazebo/pull-requests/829/clean-up-shutdown-19\" rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"ap-connect-link\">pull request #829</a> and <a href=\"#!/osrf/gazebo/pull-requests/831/clean-up-shutdown-20\" rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"ap-connect-link\">pull request #831</a>, I saw <code>gzclient</code> hang a couple of times when shutdown soon (but not immediately) after start.  It's tricky to trigger, and I can't do it reliably.  It looks like the hang is due to the model database update thread not exiting.</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "assignee": {"display_name": "Brian Gerkey", "uuid": "{3d8b5763-9dad-4be7-85c2-a7ab6cd49173}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7B3d8b5763-9dad-4be7-85c2-a7ab6cd49173%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7B3d8b5763-9dad-4be7-85c2-a7ab6cd49173%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "https://avatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.net/557058:2e35028e-9ad8-4d6a-a3a5-275159a304a9/5fa9ec73-0fec-4860-a202-e34ae23b6a12/128"}}, "nickname": "Brian Gerkey", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:2e35028e-9ad8-4d6a-a3a5-275159a304a9"}, "state": "new", "version": {"name": "all", "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo/versions/225575.json"}}}, "edited_on": null, "created_on": "2013-11-12T19:31:22.784967+00:00", "milestone": null, "updated_on": "2016-09-14T19:21:01.011896+00:00", "type": "issue", "id": 949}